comments.content: Can someone please help me identify the font ?

It looks like a very crudely traced version of a higher-res original.

I don't know the name of the original woodtype source, but the digital typeface Red Dog Saloon comes very close:  
 [http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/red-dog-saloon/](http://web.archive.org/web/20141028211716/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/red-dog-saloon/ "http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/red-dog-saloon/")

Probably based on Rodeo; here's one digital version...

[http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/baselinefonts/57-rodeo/](http://web.archive.org/web/20141028211716/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/baselinefonts/57-rodeo/ "http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/baselinefonts/57-rodeo/")
